  "commentary": "**DEALER HEDGING COMMENTARY:**\n\nWith SPX at 6811.9 sitting right between massive negative gamma walls at 6800-6820 (-200B+ combined), dealers are in full amplification mode and likely buying this dip aggressively as spot approaches the 6800 max negative gamma strike. The breakout regime with -222B total GEX means dealers will continue chasing momentum - buying any further weakness toward 6800 and selling rallies back toward 6840 where max positive gamma sits. Key inflection is the 6800 level where dealers face maximum hedging pressure, while the wall_break and gex_surge events signal we're in a volatile transition zone.\n\n**Bottom line:** expect sharp bounces off 6800 but selling pressure into any move toward 6840.",
